school district, the author explores the legal and policy issues that arise when widely disparate world views stand in the way of political compromise on educational materials, techniques, and programs. Salomone builds a case for educational governance that places the developmental needs of the child at the center of family autonomy. She advances a plan that respects diverse values and visions of schooling while preserving the core commitments that bind our nation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aCommunity and schoolxUnited States. 0aCommunity and schoolzUnited States. 0aEducation and statexUnited States. 0aEducation and statezUnited States. 0aEducationxCurriculaxUnited States. 0aEducationxCurriculazUnited States. 0aMoral educationxUnited States. 0aMoral educationzUnited States. 0aProgrammes d'étudesxÉtats-Unis. 0aRelations école-collectivitéxÉtats-Unis. 0aSchool choicexUnited States. 0aSchool choicezUnited States. 0aÉcolesxChoixxÉtats-Unis. 0aÉducation moralexÉtats-Unis. 0aÉducationxPolitique gouvernementalexÉtats-UnisxUnited States. 7aEDUCATION / Philosophy, Theory & Social Aspects.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030012915140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300129151423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300129151/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles